type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

Editor type mappings can now be configured from a dedicated ''Editor Types'' tab under Settings in the control panel, replacing the read-only table that previously lived under the Advanced tab. Each content type shows a dropdown of the editors available in the wiki, so installing an editor plugin (such as CodeMirror) is immediately selectable without manually editing the mapping tiddlers.

To make the dropdown reliable, widget modules can now declare `widget-name` and `widget-category` tiddler fields in their file headers. Editor widgets use `widget-category: editor` and a `widget-name` matching the value expected by `$:/config/EditorTypeMappings/` (for example `text`, `bitmap`, `binary`, `codemirror`). Because the metadata lives in tiddler fields rather than JavaScript exports, it can be read and parsed statically without executing the module. The dropdown is populated with `[[widget]modules[]] :filter[get[widget-category]match[editor]] :map[get[widget-name]]`, so only genuine tiddler content editors appear — widgets that merely happen to share the `edit-` prefix (such as `edit-shortcut`) are no longer listed.
